                                                                                           rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralProcessingOperation> ;
                                                                                           rdfs:comment "METSO Handbook : Grinding is the stage of size reduction (wet or dry) where the liberation size for individual minerals can be reached. By further size reduction filler (mineral powder) is produced."@en ,
                                                                                                        """MWEI BREF : Comminution process yielding a fine product (< 1 mm), where size reduction 
is accomplished by abrasion and impact and sometimes supported by the free 
motion of unconnected media such as rods, balls and pebbles."""@en .


