###  http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/LaboratoryAnalysisOperation
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/LaboratoryAnalysisOperation> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                     rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/ExplorationOperation> ;
                                                                                                     rdfs:comment "As per D9.1, this term coined as analysis" ,
                                                                                                                  "D2.1: Laboratory analyses are essential to deepen the characterization of materials present in MWFs, aiming to evaluate their potential for recovery or management." ,
                                                                                                                  """This class has been created on the bais D2.2 Section 4.2.1.4


Secondly on the basis of previous data received from the partners:
Q4: The size and extent of the waste
Mineralogy- XRD
SEM/EDS
Electron probe microanalysis (EPMA)
https://confluence.akka.eu/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=AKRSCIMIN&title=Data+Analysis+of+WP2+SGS""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/LandImpact
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/LandImpact> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                    rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/EnvironmentalImpact> .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/LeachingOperation
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/LeachingOperation> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                           rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralProcessingOperation> ;
                                                                                           rdfs:comment """MWEI BREF : Extraction of soluble components from raw materials by the action of a percolating liquid (e.g. water). For example, gold can be extracted by heap 
leaching of a porous ore, or pulverised extractive waste from mineral  processing. Other methods are tank leaching of ore, concentrates or extractive waste from mineral processing and in-situ leaching. Leaching may also be an unwanted process leading to polluted drainage (see \"leachate\"). Bio-leaching is a particular form of leaching involving living organisms"""@en .


