###  http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningLCA
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningLCA> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/LCA> ;
                                                                                   rdfs:comment "LCA in mining is a systematic method for identifying, quantifying, and evaluating the environmental impacts associated with the entire life cycle of mining-related processes and products, from exploration and extraction to processing, transportation, use, and end-of-life management." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWaste
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWaste> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                     rdfs:comment """MWEI BREF : Waste resulting from the prospecting, extraction, treatment and storage of 
mineral resources and the working of quarries"""@en ,
                                                                                                  "Mining activity exploits a mineral deposit, obtaining a concentrate (mineral object of the activity) and waste." ,
                                                                                                  """Subclass of Mining Waste from INSPIRE ontology

Note: for URI consult to INSPIRE Team""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWasteFacility
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWasteFacility> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                             rdfs:comment """MWEI BREF : Any area under the responsibility of an operator where extractive waste is 
handled, treated, accumulated or deposited whether in a solid or liquid state or 
in solution or suspension. This includes, but is not limited to, Extractive 
Waste Facilities, excavation voids where extractive waste is placed back, and 
areas for temporary storage of extractive waste."""@en ,
                                                                                                          "A mining waste facility is a designated site or structure used to store extractive waste (includes materials like waste rock and tailings from mining and mineral processing operations)." ,
                                                                                                          """Mining Waste Facilities (MWF): (SCIMIN-GA)
defined by JRC as any area designated for the accumulation or deposit of extractive waste, whether in solid or liquid state or in solution or suspension, derived from extracting & processing mineral resources. 
Reference Grant Agreement (GA).

Mining Waste (INSPIRE Model)
Mining waste can be defined as a part of the materials that result from the exploration, mining and processing of substances governed by legislation on mines and quarries.""" ,
                                                                                                          """sublcass of mining wasting  from INSPIRE

Note: for URI, we need to consult INSPIRE team because current it is not mentioned in specification document and nor on website""" .


